===Alternative forms===
{{wikipedia}}
* [[aard-vark]]

===Etymology===
{{etyl|af}} from {{term|aarde||earth|lang=af}}, and {{term|vark||pig|lang=af}}; hence "earth-pig". Early European colonists in South Africa noticed that the animal was similar to a pig, while "aarde" hints at the animal's habit of burrowing. The word was [[loan]]ed from {{etyl|af}} in the late 18th century.

===Pronunciation===
{{wikisource1911Enc|Aard-vark}}
